<br>
Molto Espressivo, the All Bard Guild on Firona Vie was started in January of 2003 as an experiment in all-bard grouping, and bard-heavy grouping.  We have since grown into a sizable guild, with a very active core membership of about 30 Bards ranging from levels 40 - 63.<br>
<br>
Molto was born on the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub142.ezboard.com/beqdivabardsofeverquest">EQdiva messageboards</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, and has among it's members some very experienced, respected, and knowledgable bards from that community.  We have been attending as many open raids as we can in an effort to make our name and our skills known.<br>
<br>
It is time that Molto Espressivo established formal alliances with other guilds.  Whereas Molto is very proud of our track record of accomplishments using non-traditional and creative tactics to make Bard-only and bard-heavy groups succeed, clearly, high-end named mobs cannot be killed without more traditional raid tactics.<br>
<br>
Our desires for Alliances:<br>
<br>
1)  For those who seek alliance with us, we will be &quot;your Bards&quot; for raiding.  That is, we will attend your raids as if we were members of your guild, whenever RL allows.<br>
<br>
2)  First-Come, First-Served.  Whichever guild approaches us first, and formalizes an Alliance relationship with us will have first priority in our scheduling.  For example, Guild A became our Ally before Guild B.  Both guilds schedule a Friday night raid.  Guild A will have our support, because they sought us first for alliance.<br>
<br>
3)  We want full particiaption in whatever the looting scheme is for our Allied guilds.  If your guild uses some form of DKP, we want to be on the list to earn points.  If your guild has waiting periods, etc. that is fine with us too.  Since we will be &quot;your bards&quot; we wish to be included as if we belonged to your guild.<br>
<br>
4)  We are not a &quot;Roleplay-heavy&quot; guild, and do not have requirements or restrictions for our members on alignments, grouping etc.  We certainly respect people who do RP more fervently than we, and will respect whatever raid guidelines our Allies have for their raids.  (We also have different RP playing styles among our members as well, btw.)<br>
<br>
5)  Our Alignment, for those who are concerned about such things, is Good and/or Neutral.  We are on Dwarf and CoV faction in Vellious (we kill giants, hehe).<br>
<br>
If your Guild may be interested, if you have questions for us, or would like to invite us to a raid to see what we are like, I encourage you to /join Molto channel and give us a holler.  Or, send me a tell ingame.  Or, post here or in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub142.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm83">our Forum at EQdiva.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
